  "prompt": "How do I search if any of my friends and relatives are here on Quora?",
  "response": "To check if any of your friends or relatives are on Quora, you can follow these steps:\n\n1. **Sign In to Quora**: Log into your Quora account. If you don\u2019t have one, you will need to create an account.\n\n2. **Profile Search**: Use the search bar at the top of the Quora homepage. You can search for your friends or relatives by typing their names. Quora may also suggest people you might know based on your interests and the questions you follow.\n\n3. **Connect Your Contacts**: Quora allows you to connect your email or social media accounts (like Facebook) to find people you know. This option usually appears in your account settings or under your profile settings. After connecting, Quora will suggest users from your contacts who are also on the platform.\n\n4. **Explore Topics**: If you know certain topics your friends and relatives are interested in, you can search for those topics and see if they are following or contributing to discussions on those subjects.\n\n5. **Check Followers and Following Lists**: If you find someone you suspect could be a friend or relative, check their followers and who they are following to see if you recognize any names.\n\nIf you don't find anyone initially, try variations of names or check back later, as people join Quora frequently.",
